  <main class="content wrap">
    <h1>About Bee Planet Connection</h1>
    <p>We serve global apiculture as an open hub for knowledge, tools, a directory, and discussion &mdash; championing environmental stewardship in beekeeping.</p>

    <h2>What BPC is</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>A free knowledge base:</strong> An open wiki of referenced articles from bee biology to best practices.</li>
      <li><strong>A practical toolkit:</strong> Templates, checklists, and calculators for day-to-day and seasonal tasks.</li>
      <li><strong>A global directory:</strong> Organisations, research bodies, and networks in apiculture.</li>
      <li><strong>A community forum:</strong> Thoughtful discussion, Q&A, and peer support.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What BPC is not</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Not a marketplace.</li>
      <li>Not a regulatory authority &mdash; always follow local rules and veterinary advice.</li>
      <li>Not a closed club &mdash; we welcome constructive contributions from all.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contribute</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Suggest edits via GitHub pull requests.</li>
      <li>Propose directory additions.</li>
      <li>Share tools and templates.</li>
      <li>Join discussions and mentor newcomers.</li>
    </ul>
  </main>

  <footer class="site-footer wrap">
    <p>? 2025 Bee Planet Connection &mdash; For bees, for people, for planet.</p>
